// SCSA-1220: CPU Architecture Definition
// Word Size: 1220-bit (Infinite Compute)

[CONTROL_UNIT]
Type: Hyper-Scale Decoder & State Counter
Output: 1220-bit Control Signals (Load_A, ALU_Sel, Mem_W/R, etc.)

[INTERNAL_BUS]
Type: 1220-bit Data Path

[ACCUMULATOR (A)]
Size: 1220-bit Register (Hyper-Scale Flip-Flops)

[ARITHMETIC_LOGIC_UNIT (ALU)]
Size: 1220-bit Logic (Single Cycle Operation)
Function: 1220-bit ADD, SUB, AND, OR, XOR, SHIFT (All 1220-bit in one cycle)

[RAM]
Type: Hyper-Scale Memory (Conceptual)
Capacity: 2^1220 Addresses (Theoretical Infinity)
Data In/Out: 1220-bit

[I/O_UNIT]
Type: PSI/O Manager (Secure Terminal, Network Stack)
